text.tspan: Recipient Status States
Creator: This is an OU user that has the entitlement to create recipients, and has created a recipient that has been
sent for approval.
Editor: The person who created a recipient, or the person who edited a recipient last. Whenever a recipient is edited,
the Editor is updated to whomever made the changes. Until a pending recipient is approved to active status, only the
person who last edited or created (whichever happened most recently) can edit the pending recipient again. This
restricts the editing of a pending recipient to only one user.
Entitled: Any user who has the entitlements to create a recipient.
Authorizer: A user who has the entitlements to approve or decline a recipient.
User Types
Create: This is when a new recipient is created. This puts the recipient in Pending status which is awaiting approval
(Approval Pending or Approval Required depending on what user is viewing the recipient). The comment for a create
action in the Activity Log table is the same comment entered by the Creator when entering Basic Information in the
Recipient Creation flow.
Approve: When a recipient is approved, the status is changed to Active. The Authorizer can enter an optional
comment when approving a recipient during the Approve Recipient flow, which is what will appear in the Activity Log
table.
Sent Back: A sent back recipient will have its status updated to Sent Back, and can be found by only the Editor in the
Pending Recipient table found through the Recipient Landing page. This sends a pending recipient back to the Editor
for changes to be made, to be deleted, or will be automatically deleted if not actioned upon within X days. The
Authorizer can enter an optional comment when sending back a recipient during the Send Back Recipient flow, which
is what will appear in the Activity Log table.
Edit: Only the Creator or Editor of a recipient can edit a pending recipient, once a pending recipient has been edited it
must be approved in order to become an active recipient. Active recipients can be edited by anyone who has the
entitlement to create a new recipient.
The comment that appears in the Activity Log table is automatically generated based on what recipient information has
been edited, in the format of “<Type of recipient information> updated.” For example, if the account information has
been updated, the comment that would appear in the Activity Log table would be, “Account Information updated.”.
Whenever a recipient is edited, the Editor is updated to whomever made the changes.
Suspend: Active recipients can be suspended so that they cannot have payments made to them, and any pending
payments cannot be approved and will be turned into a draft payment and therefore moved to the draft payments table
on the Payment Landing page. The Authorizer can enter an optional comment when suspending a recipient during the
Suspend Recipient flow, which is what will appear in the Activity Log table.
Reactivate: This removes the suspended status of a recipient, changing the status of the recipient back to active. This
effectively allows payments to be made to the recipient once again. The Authorizer can enter an optional comment
when reactivating a recipient during the Reactivate Recipient flow, which is what will appear in the Activity Log table.
Delete: Deleting a recipient can be done by users with the same entitlements to create a recipient, with the exception
of approvers in the specific situation where a recipient requires approval. When an Approver is approving a recipient,
they cannot delete it, they will only have the option to approve or Send Back the recipient. This limits deletion to the
Editor of a recipient and adheres to proper approval process. A recipient can also be deleted automatically by the
system if it has been in “Sent Back” status for more than XX days.
Deleting a recipient removes the recipient from the Recipient Landing page for OU users, allowing only DBank
employees to view the deleted recipient. With this, OU users can find related payment history for the deleted recipient
within the Payments Landing page, if payments have been created for the recipient. The comment that appears in the
Activity Log table is automatically generated to say, “Recipient deleted.”. Since deleted recipients cannot be viewed by
OU users, only DBank employees will be able to view this comment.
All actions are recorded in the Activity Log table found in Recipient Detail pages:

Pending: Every time a recipient is sent to pending, the “editor” is the person who did an action to put the recipient in
pending status. There are three statuses that are considered pending:
Active: Payments can be made to this Recipient. Anyone who has the entitlements to do so can edit this recipient,
sending it back to Pending for authorization.
Suspended: Status of a recipient that has all the capabilities of an active recipient except that no payments can be
made to this recipient.
Deleted: Recipients with this status cannot be found by OU users, this is completely removed from Recipient Landing
page. Can be found by DBank employees.
Approval Required: A pending recipient that requires an authorizer’s approval. This status is seen by Authorizers
who are not the editor of the pending Recipient.
Approval Pending: A recipient that requires action from another OU user. This is seen by users who do not have
entitlements to action the pending recipient (whether the user does not have the entitlements or is the creator/
editor of the recipient), as well as users who have already been approved and need to be approved by 1+ other
users.
Sent Back: Status of a recipient sent back by the Authorizer, and needs to be actioned by the editor. Actions
include to edit the recipient so that it can be resubmitted for authorization, or to be deleted. If nothing is done by
the editor in XX days the sent back recipient gets deleted automatically by the system. Sent back recipients are
only viewable by the editor.
